1 A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
2 AN ACT TO UPDATE AND CLARIFY THE NORTH CAROLINA ENGINEERING AND
3 LAND SURVEYING ACT, MODIFYING LICENSURE REQUIREMENTS, BOARD
4 POWERS, DISCIPLINARY PROCEDURES, AND OTHER PROVISIONS TO ENHANCE
5 PROFESSIONAL REGULATION AND PRACTICE.
6 The General Assembly of North Carolina enacts:
7 SECTION 1.(a) Land Surveyor Intern Reenactment. – G.S. 89C-3(4) is reenacted as
8 it existed immediately before its repeal under Section 1(a) of S.L. 2022-1 and shall be recodified
9 as subdivision (4b) of that section to ensure the subdivisions of G.S. 89C-3 are listed in
10 alphabetical order and make any conforming changes in the General Statutes to reflect this
11 recodification.
12 SECTION 1.(b) G.S. 89C-13(b)(1) is reenacted as it existed immediately before its
13 repeal under Section 1(b) of S.L. 2022-1.
14 SECTION 1.(c) Applicability. – This section is effective retroactively to July 1,
15 2022, and applies to certificates or licenses issued on or after that date.
16 SECTION 2.(a) G.S. 89C-3 reads as rewritten:
17 "§ 89C-3. Definitions.
18 The following definitions apply in this Chapter:
19 …
20 (7) Practice of land surveying. –
21 a. Providing professional services such as consultation, investigation,
22 testimony, evaluation, planning, mapping, assembling, and
23 interpreting reliable scientific measurements and information relative
24 to the location, size, shape, or physical features of the earth,
25 improvements on the earth, the space above the earth, or any part of
26 the earth, whether the gathering of information for the providing of
27 these services is accomplished by conventional ground measurements,
28 by aerial photography, by global positioning via satellites, or by a
29 combination of any of these methods, and the utilization and
30 development of these facts and interpretations into an orderly survey
31 map, plan, report, description, or project. The practice of land
32 surveying includes the following:
33 1. Locating, relocating, establishing, laying out, or retracing any
34 property line, easement, or boundary of any tract of land;
