3 (2) Landowner. – The owner, lessee, or occupant of a parcel of land.
4 (3) Practice of land surveying. – As defined in G.S. 89C-3.
5 (4) Professional land surveyor. – As defined in G.S. 89C-3. For purposes of this
6 section, this term includes any agents, employees, or personnel under the
7 supervision of a professional land surveyor.
8 (b) A professional land surveyor shall have the right to enter upon the lands of others, if
9 necessary to perform surveys for the practice of land surveying, including the location of property
10 corners, boundary lines, rights-of-way, and easements, and may carry with them their customary
11 equipment and vehicles. An entry by a professional land surveyor to perform the practice of land
12 surveying under this section shall not constitute trespass under this Article or Article 22A of this
13 Chapter and shall not cause the professional land surveyor to be subject to arrest or a civil action
14 by reason of the entry.
15 (c) Nothing in this section shall be construed as giving authority to a professional land
16 surveyor to destroy, injure, damage, or move anything on the lands of another without the written
17 permission of the landowner, and nothing in this section shall be construed as removing civil
18 liability for such damage.
19 (d) No professional land surveyor shall have a civil cause of action against a landowner
20 for personal injury or property damage incurred while on the land for purposes consistent with
21 those described in subsection (b) of this section, except when such damages and injury were
22 willfully or deliberately caused by the landowner.
23 (e) Nothing in this section shall be construed as giving authority to a professional land
24 surveyor to do the following:
25 (1) Enter lands traversed by an operating railroad or properties owned, held, used,
26 or operated by a railroad or their subsidiaries.
27 (2) Enter lands containing critical infrastructure."
28 SECTION 3.(c) This section applies to acts on or after its effective date.
29 SECTION 4. Rulemaking. – The Board of Examiners for Engineers and Surveyors
30 may adopt rules to implement the provisions of this act.
31 SECTION 5. Effective Date. – Sections 2 and 4 of this act become effective October
32 1, 2025. Except as otherwise provided, this act is effective when it becomes law.
